kernel_variant.question:
Let S be a subset of the rational numbers such that
(a) 0\in S;
(b) x\in S  \Rightarrow   x+1\in S and x-1\in S;
(c) x\in S and x\notin {0,1}  \Rightarrow   1/[x(x-1)]\in S.

Is it necessary that S contain every rational number?  Justify your answer.
